# Copy credentials file (not this example) to .htpasswd next to this file:
#   backend/config/.htpasswd
#
# Generate (first user):
#   htpasswd -c /home/USER/posutki/backend/config/.htpasswd USERNAME
#
# Add another user:
#   htpasswd /home/USER/posutki/backend/config/.htpasswd OTHER
#
# cPanel: "Directory Privacy" can create .htpasswd too — point AuthUserFile in
# public/.htaccess to that file, or copy the generated file to backend/config/.htpasswd
#
# /api and /uploads are not protected — only URIs starting with /admin (see public/.htaccess).
